CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779203471
OL,3,CMan Utd's Ella Toone and darts
OL,4,Cchampion Luke Littler to receive MBEs
OL,6,FLittler, who became the youngest world
OL,7,Fchampion in the history of darts aged
OL,8,F17 years and 347 days, was made an MBE
OL,9,Ffor services to the sport in the
OL,10,FKing's Birthday Honours last year.
OL,12,FThe 19-year-old, currently ranked
OL,13,Fworld number one, is widely credited
OL,14,Fwith boosting the profile of the sport
OL,15,Falongside darts great Luke Humphries.
OL,17,FHumphries praised Littler for bringing
OL,18,Fa "massive new crowd" to darts as he
OL,19,Freceived his own honour from the
OL,20,FPrince of Wales in May.
OL,26,@zD@COUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
